3. Specific Requirements
3.1 Core Game State Requirements

3.1.0 The system shall maintain a single GameState object as the authoritative source of truth for all game data.
3.1.1 The GameState shall contain currentScore.
3.1.2 The GameState shall contain remainingTime.
3.1.3 The GameState shall contain targetScore.
3.1.4 The GameState shall contain boardState.
3.1.5 The GameState shall contain gameStatus with possible values: RUNNING, WON, LOST.
3.1.6 Only the RulesEngine and GameController shall modify GameState.
3.1.7 Invalid placement attempts shall not modify GameState.

3.2 Board and Square Requirements

3.2.0 The system shall initialize a fixed-size 2D Board grid at game start.
3.2.1 The Board shall contain Square objects.
3.2.2 Each Square shall maintain row and column position.
3.2.3 Each Square shall maintain an occupied flag.
3.2.4 Each Square shall maintain a bonusType value (NONE, POINTS, TIME).
3.2.5 Each Square shall maintain a bonusValue.
3.2.6 A Square marked as occupied shall not accept additional tiles.
3.2.7 Bonus squares shall apply their effect only once when first used.
3.2.8 After a bonus is applied, the square shall revert to a non-bonus state.

3.3 Tile Requirements

3.3.0 Each Tile shall contain a character.
3.3.1 Each Tile shall contain a pointValue or derive scoring from word length logic.
3.3.2 Tiles shall only be placed onto unoccupied Squares.
3.3.3 Tile placement shall occur only through validated PlacementRequest processing.

3.4 Word Placement and Validation Requirements

3.4.0 All moves shall be submitted through a PlacementRequest.
3.4.1 A PlacementRequest shall include a word string.
3.4.2 A PlacementRequest shall include a starting position.
3.4.3 A PlacementRequest shall include a direction (horizontal or vertical).

3.4.4 The RulesEngine shall validate that the placement fits within board boundaries (validatePlacementFitsBoard).
3.4.5 The RulesEngine shall validate minimum word length (validateMinimumWordLength).
3.4.6 The RulesEngine shall validate square availability (validateSquareAvailability).
3.4.7 If validation fails, the move shall be rejected with no state mutation.
3.4.8 If validation succeeds, the GameController shall proceed with scoring and state update.

3.5 Scoring Requirements

3.5.0 All scoring shall be handled by ScoreCalculator.
3.5.1 The ScoreCalculator shall compute base score using calculateBaseScore(wordLength).
3.5.2 The ScoreCalculator shall apply square bonuses using applyBonusPoints(squareBonus).
3.5.3 The ScoreCalculator shall return the totalScore for the move.
3.5.4 Scoring logic shall be deterministic.
3.5.5 Scoring logic shall not depend on the UI layer.
3.5.6 The GameController shall add the returned totalScore to GameState.currentScore.

3.6 Time System Requirements

3.6.0 The system shall initialize the TimeManager with initialTimeLimit.
3.6.1 The TimeManager shall decrement time continuously during RUNNING state.
3.6.2 Time bonuses shall only originate from Squares with bonusType = TIME.
3.6.3 The TimeManager shall apply time bonuses using applyTimeBonus.
3.6.4 The TimeManager shall evaluate expiration using checkTimeExpired.
3.6.5 If time expires, the EndConditionEvaluator shall trigger loss state.

3.7 End Condition Requirements

3.7.0 EndConditionEvaluator shall check win condition using checkWinCondition(score, targetScore).
3.7.1 A win shall occur when currentScore >= targetScore.
3.7.2 EndConditionEvaluator shall check lose condition using checkLoseCondition(timeRemaining).
3.7.3 A loss shall occur when remainingTime <= 0.
3.7.4 Upon win, GameState.gameStatus shall be set to WON.
3.7.5 Upon loss, GameState.gameStatus shall be set to LOST.
3.7.6 No additional moves shall be accepted when gameStatus is not RUNNING.

3.8 Game Flow Control Requirements

3.8.0 All placement input shall be processed by GameController.
3.8.1 GameController shall call RulesEngine for validation.
3.8.2 Upon successful validation, GameController shall update GameState.
3.8.3 GameController shall trigger ScoreCalculator for scoring.
3.8.4 GameController shall trigger TimeManager updates as needed.
3.8.5 After each move, GameController shall invoke EndConditionEvaluator.

3.9 UI Layer Requirements

3.9.0 GameUI shall render the Board using renderBoard(boardState).
3.9.1 GameUI shall display currentScore using displayScore.
3.9.2 GameUI shall display remainingTime using displayTime.
3.9.3 GameUI shall display gameStatus using displayGameStatus.
3.9.4 GameUI shall collect word input via collectWordInput.
3.9.5 GameUI shall collect placement input via collectPlacementInput.
3.9.6 The UI layer shall not directly modify GameState.

3.10 Persistence Requirements

3.10.0 SaveManager shall serialize GameState to a local file.
3.10.1 SaveManager shall deserialize GameState from a local file.
3.10.2 Save/load operations shall not modify core game logic.
3.10.3 Loading a saved game shall restore Board state, score, time, and gameStatus.

3.11 Testing Surface Requirements

3.11.0 RulesEngine shall be testable independently of UI.
3.11.1 ScoreCalculator shall be testable independently.
3.11.2 TimeManager shall be testable independently.
3.11.3 EndConditionEvaluator shall be testable independently.
3.11.4 All validation failures shall produce deterministic results for test reproducibility.
